    "body": "I stumbled on this issue, as I got confused on why `forge remappings` command was *not* picking up my changes in foundry.toml, neither in .dapprc. The doc says the following about this command: \"prints the automatically inferred remappings for this repository\". Maybe we should either update the documentation, or change the command behaviour? IMO it would be useful if this command actually printed the final result (after reading all config files, env vars) with the effective configuration.\r\n(man forge says I'm on version 0.2.0. `forge --version` yields command not found. Maybe i'm on a too old version? \r\n\r\nEdit: Hm.. it looks like I was \"stuck\" in some old forge version, that wasn't even picking up the foundry.toml.\r\n\r\nNow on 0.2.0 ef881b75  , but still it seems foundry.toml is not being used \r\n\nEdit 2: please ignore all the above. On another machine with clean installation it works as expected. ",
